# Design tokens — read-only for the agent

Never modify token source files or files generated from them. Tokens flow from Figma via Tokens Studio; the build pipeline produces CSS output.

## Do not edit

- `src/tokens/*.json` — source of truth, synced from Figma/Tokens Studio (multifile: one JSON per token set + `$metadata.json`)
- `dist/variables.css` — auto-generated CSS custom properties

These files include an `AUTO-GENERATED` banner. Treat them as read-only.

## Allowed changes

- `style-dictionary.config.js` — build pipeline / output format only
- Running `npm run build:tokens` to regenerate `dist/variables.css` after the user syncs tokens from Figma

## When tokens need to change

1. User updates tokens in Figma and syncs via Tokens Studio → `src/tokens/*.json`
2. Run `npm run build:tokens` (or let CI) to regenerate `dist/variables.css`
3. Consumers reference `var(--ds-*)` from that stylesheet
